OL,6,F"Whilst the expert opinion provides us
OL,7,Fwith assurance that the proper
OL,8,Fcrematorium process had been followed,
OL,9,Funfortunately, given the high
OL,10,Ftemperature required to carry out a
OL,11,Fcremation, the DNA will have been
OL,12,Fbroken down and degraded to such a
OL,13,Flevel, that we would not be able to
OL,14,Frecover a meaningful DNA profile.
OL,16,F"This means that we are unable to
OL,17,Fidentify any of the human ashes.
